98
00:07:00,448 --> 00:07:01,883
I know.

99
00:07:06,855 --> 00:07:09,176
Have a good trip.

100
00:07:57,319 --> 00:07:59,839
Go, Henry, go!

101
00:07:59,939 --> 00:08:02,360
Let's go! Come on!

102
00:08:06,923 --> 00:08:07,780
Way to go, Henry!

103
00:08:07,890 --> 00:08:10,540
Now stay with him! Stay with him!

104
00:08:10,649 --> 00:08:13,539
Come on! Back, back! Back!

105
00:08:15,133 --> 00:08:16,358
Go, Henry!

106
00:08:18,720 --> 00:08:21,509
Go! Shoot it! Shoot it!

107
00:08:29,420 --> 00:08:29,978
Whoo!

108
00:08:30,078 --> 00:08:31,821
- Get him, Henry!
- Get him, Henry!

109
00:08:31,921 --> 00:08:33,077
Yeah! Whoo!

110
00:08:33,186 --> 00:08:35,338
Looks like Henry's got a
little fan club going.

111
00:08:39,064 --> 00:08:41,057
Theo's kicking butt today.

112
00:08:41,157 --> 00:08:42,552
I taught him everything he knows.

113
00:08:44,753 --> 00:08:46,507
Way to go, Jordy!

114
00:08:46,617 --> 00:08:49,237
Come on!

115
00:08:55,125 --> 00:08:57,247
They were all so man-hungry.

116
00:08:57,347 --> 00:08:58,812
Lyudmila, anyway.

117
00:08:58,911 --> 00:09:03,165
And the families, with
money-- it was all so...

118
00:09:03,265 --> 00:09:04,401
Normal?

119
00:09:04,501 --> 00:09:06,224
And the way they lived in the beginning,

120
00:09:06,324 --> 00:09:08,416
it was like my freshman-year dorm.

121
00:09:08,516 --> 00:09:11,843
I lived in a workers'
dormitory when I was young.

122
00:09:11,943 --> 00:09:15,072
It was hard work, but
we had a lot of fun.

123
00:09:15,171 --> 00:09:16,397
Really?

124
00:09:16,496 --> 00:09:18,559
We would sneak boys in at night.

125
00:09:18,658 --> 00:09:20,223
That's why I live off-campus.

126
00:09:20,322 --> 00:09:22,683
I thought Katerina was great.

127
00:09:22,783 --> 00:09:26,041
Yeah, she was so determined. And brave.

128
00:09:26,141 --> 00:09:27,834
She reminded me of you, Mom.

129
00:09:27,934 --> 00:09:29,359
Thank you.

130
00:09:29,468 --> 00:09:30,893
In that skirt suit, with the vest,

131
00:09:30,993 --> 00:09:32,109
running that whole factory.

132
00:09:32,148 --> 00:09:33,782
- Fantastic.
- Yeah.

133
00:09:33,882 --> 00:09:35,576
That's how it is there.

134
00:09:35,685 --> 00:09:38,475
But then she let that guy--

135
00:09:38,575 --> 00:09:39,870
put her in her place.

136
00:09:39,880 --> 00:09:41,165
Like... dominate her.

137
00:09:41,265 --> 00:09:42,929
I hated that.

138
00:09:43,028 --> 00:09:46,486
Sometimes it's a little
more traditional there.

139
00:09:46,585 --> 00:09:52,065
But some women I know would
have cracked his head open.

140
00:09:54,396 --> 00:09:57,116
Did your professor talk about
the Summit again this week?

141
00:09:57,226 --> 00:10:00,613
He spent the whole class talking
about the Soviet SS-20.

142
00:10:00,713 --> 00:10:02,437
What did he say?

143
00:10:02,536 --> 00:10:04,738
It's got a range of 3,100 miles,

144
00:10:04,838 --> 00:10:06,063
can carry up to three

145
00:10:06,163 --> 00:10:07,817
independently targetable warheads,

146
00:10:07,837 --> 00:10:11,244
each with an explosive
power of 150 kilotons.

147
00:10:11,354 --> 00:10:13,845
And it can be launched
from the back of a truck.

148
00:10:13,944 --> 00:10:17,073
After an hour of that, in the
last two minutes of class,

149
00:10:17,192 --> 00:10:19,524
he said if the Summit's a success,

150
00:10:19,623 --> 00:10:22,513
there won't be any SS-20s anymore.

151
00:10:22,622 --> 00:10:24,416
So you learned all that for nothing.

152
00:10:24,515 --> 00:10:27,574
He thinks the Summit's
going to be a big success.

153
00:10:27,674 --> 00:10:29,298
It's hard to trust the Americans.

154
00:10:29,397 --> 00:10:32,356
There's a long history of
these types of negotiations.

155
00:10:32,456 --> 00:10:34,020
I know.

156
00:10:34,120 --> 00:10:36,152
Okay. You want a ride
back to your apartment?

157
00:10:36,232 --> 00:10:37,846
- Yeah.
- Wait in the car.

158
00:10:37,946 --> 00:10:38,972
Okay.

159
00:10:39,071 --> 00:10:39,938
See ya.

160
00:10:40,038 --> 00:10:41,204
Mm.

161
00:10:43,425 --> 00:10:44,322
Keep your eyes open.

162
00:10:44,432 --> 00:10:45,986
Mm-hmm.

163
00:10:51,077 --> 00:10:53,269
I saw McCleesh, coming out of DoE.

164
00:10:53,369 --> 00:10:54,833
He was with some negotiators

165
00:10:54,933 --> 00:10:57,852
for the ground-launched
missile verification regime.

166
00:10:57,962 --> 00:10:59,885
I'm going to see him soon.

167
00:11:01,618 --> 00:11:02,903
I was at Haskard's Tuesday night.

168
00:11:03,013 --> 00:11:05,165
I couldn't get to the
briefcase. Back there tonight.

169
00:11:05,275 --> 00:11:09,021
And then Voller again Thursday.

170
00:11:09,888 --> 00:11:11,751
Are you sleeping?

171
00:11:12,687 --> 00:11:14,012
Sure.

172
00:11:14,112 --> 00:11:16,374
You got nine weeks to the Summit.

173
00:11:19,004 --> 00:11:20,130
I got a signal.

174
00:11:20,230 --> 00:11:21,993
You have a meeting in
Mexico. Tomorrow morning.

175
00:11:22,093 --> 00:11:25,849
I don't know who it's
with or what it's about.

176
00:11:25,948 --> 00:11:28,140
They didn't tell you anything?

177
00:11:28,838 --> 00:11:30,402
It happens.

178
00:11:36,918 --> 00:11:39,478
I can't believe what Moscow looks like.

179
00:11:40,305 --> 00:11:43,235
You could've been one of
those silly little girls.

180
00:11:47,688 --> 00:11:48,983
Mm.

