00:40:29,950 --> 00:40:32,680
I wish I could, but my friend
and I already have plans.

568
00:40:32,780 --> 00:40:33,976
Next time.

569
00:40:34,075 --> 00:40:37,961
Okay. Well, here's your
driver's license, okay?

570
00:40:38,061 --> 00:40:39,694
I'm gonna hold on to
this other one, though.

571
00:40:39,794 --> 00:40:40,990
You can get it back Saturday night

572
00:40:41,089 --> 00:40:42,713
after I take you to dinner.

573
00:40:43,680 --> 00:40:44,676
Call you tomorrow.

574
00:40:44,776 --> 00:40:46,968
Oh, come on. You can't
take my college ID.

575
00:40:47,077 --> 00:40:47,854
I need it.

576
00:40:47,894 --> 00:40:49,967
I-I promise I'll meet you Saturday.

577
00:40:50,893 --> 00:40:52,627
I don't know, beautiful
girl like yourself

578
00:40:52,726 --> 00:40:53,683
might forget, you know.

579
00:40:53,792 --> 00:40:55,915
I couldn't forget you.

580
00:40:57,280 --> 00:40:58,246
That was a nice try.

581
00:40:58,346 --> 00:41:00,039
I'll see you Saturday, Ellen.

582
00:41:11,407 --> 00:41:13,171
You must miss your girls, being her.

583
00:41:13,271 --> 00:41:14,566
Uh, before I leave,

584
00:41:14,665 --> 00:41:17,326
they are sweetest they have ever been.

585
00:41:17,425 --> 00:41:19,418
Aha. And school?

586
00:41:19,517 --> 00:41:21,829
Both smarter than me. I can admit this.

587
00:41:21,909 --> 00:41:24,001
My Katya, she is serious.

588
00:41:29,521 --> 00:41:32,081
He was going for Chinese food
at a place called Hunan Taste.

589
00:41:32,181 --> 00:41:33,745
That's the only reason he was out there.

590
00:41:33,845 --> 00:41:35,807
N. Hadley. Blue eyes. 5'11".

591
00:41:35,907 --> 00:41:37,969
US Naval Observatory patch on his hat.

592
00:41:38,069 --> 00:41:39,165
Black uniform.

593
00:41:39,265 --> 00:41:40,659
I saw everything, Mom.

594
00:41:40,759 --> 00:41:42,453
I was a mile out of the zone,
like I'm supposed to be.

595
00:41:42,552 --> 00:41:43,917
Waiting for my next shift.

596
00:41:44,017 --> 00:41:45,880
Maybe I shouldn't have been reading.

597
00:41:45,980 --> 00:41:47,972
It's okay. It's not your fault.

598
00:41:48,072 --> 00:41:49,298
I'm sorry, Mom. Damn it!

599
00:41:49,407 --> 00:41:52,296
This is-- This is part of it.
This is what happens.

600
00:41:52,396 --> 00:41:53,592
You handled it well.

601
00:41:53,691 --> 00:41:55,614
He has my ID. With my picture.

602
00:41:55,724 --> 00:41:58,075
Fake name, fake address.

603
00:41:58,185 --> 00:41:59,311
You gave him a fake phone number.

604
00:41:59,410 --> 00:42:01,572
You remembered everything. Okay?

605
00:42:01,672 --> 00:42:03,963
He's a security guard at
the US Naval Observatory.

606
00:42:04,063 --> 00:42:06,823
He's not a police officer.
This isn't a big deal.

607
00:42:09,483 --> 00:42:11,446
I really want you to understand this.

608
00:42:11,545 --> 00:42:14,455
Under pressure, you kept your cover.

609
00:42:14,534 --> 00:42:16,955
You said and did all the right things.

610
00:42:17,065 --> 00:42:18,858
There's nothing to worry about.

611
00:42:21,648 --> 00:42:23,143
Thanks.

612
00:42:45,988 --> 00:42:48,340
I need you to drop me near
Wisconsin and Calvert.

613
00:42:48,439 --> 00:42:50,203
- Is she okay?
- Yeah.

614
00:42:51,498 --> 00:42:53,590
I like Julie, but I told
you when she came on,

615
00:42:53,700 --> 00:42:54,557
she's too young.

616
00:42:54,656 --> 00:42:56,788
I have a lot of faith in this one.

617
00:42:56,888 --> 00:42:58,084
Drive.

618
00:43:14,045 --> 00:43:15,768
Wait, stop here.

619
00:43:38,544 --> 00:43:40,696
Excuse me. Sir?

620
00:43:40,796 --> 00:43:42,031
Can I help you?

621
00:43:43,765 --> 00:43:45,519
Miss?

622
00:43:45,618 --> 00:43:48,348
Yeah, uh, do you have a light?

623
00:43:48,448 --> 00:43:50,939
Yeah. Somewhere.

624
00:44:57,732 --> 00:45:00,422
I always like DC this time of year.

625
00:45:02,385 --> 00:45:06,410
I prefer it when the
cherry blossoms are out.

626
00:45:11,661 --> 00:45:13,255
You sure you're good?

627
00:45:13,653 --> 00:45:15,915
I spent nine hours getting clean.

628
00:45:16,114 --> 00:45:18,047
They'd have to have the whole FBI on me

629
00:45:18,147 --> 00:45:20,538
for me to miss it.

630
00:45:20,637 --> 00:45:21,962
Okay.

631
00:45:23,796 --> 00:45:25,828
Arkady Ivanovich sent me.

632
00:45:25,928 --> 00:45:28,648
We need your help.

633
00:45:28,747 --> 00:45:29,883
We?

634
00:45:32,743 --> 00:45:36,399
The people... running the
organization right now,

635
00:45:36,499 --> 00:45:38,760
they have very...

636
00:45:38,860 --> 00:45:41,052
old-line view of things.

637
00:45:41,979 --> 00:45:45,466
Not interested in all the
changes that are happening.

638
00:45:45,575 --> 00:45:48,823
And Gorbachev doesn't have the
power to get rid of them.

639
00:45:50,487 --> 00:45:52,649
I'm out of it.

640
00:45:52,749 --> 00:45:53,944
He told me.

641
00:45:56,077 --> 00:45:58,697
I wouldn't be here except...

642
00:46:00,600 --> 00:46:03,131
some very powerful people

643
00:46:03,150 --> 00:46:04,954
are out there to get rid of Gorbachev.

644
00:46:05,053 --> 00:46:08,132
To stop all the good things

645
00:46:08,152 --> 00:46:10,633
that have been happening
lately in our country.

646
00:46:11,539 --> 00:46:15,385
Your wife had a meeting in Latin America

647
00:46:15,495 --> 00:46:18,743
with a general from the
Strategic Rocket Forces.

648
00:46:19,809 --> 00:46:21,473
Strange, right?

649
00:46:23,206 --> 00:46:26,156
No stranger than us meeting here.

650
00:46:27,959 --> 00:46:31,845
My wife just does her job.

651
00:46:31,944 --> 00:46:33,538
That's all she's ever done.

652
00:46:33,638 --> 00:46:35,501
She's good at it.

653
00:46:35,601 --> 00:46:36,527
I know.

654
00:46:36,637 --> 00:46:39,686
But it's possible that she is being used

655
00:46:39,795 --> 00:46:42,316
by the people who are...

656
00:46:42,416 --> 00:46:46,341
trying to stop all the progress
that we've been making.

657
00:46:50,994 --> 00:46:53,754
Or she is one of them.

658
00:47:00,270 --> 00:47:03,189
Everything is divided up.

659
00:47:04,753 --> 00:47:07,881
That's how Arkady Ivanovich
explained it to me.

660
00:47:09,745 --> 00:47:13,202
This summit, it could
be a turning point.

661
00:47:14,128 --> 00:47:17,616
We have a pretty good
idea where you stand.

662
00:47:17,725 --> 00:47:19,479
I'm not involved anymore.

663
00:47:19,588 --> 00:47:22,139
And this has nothing to do with me.

664
00:47:26,363 --> 00:47:28,924
We want you to find out
what your wife is doing

665
00:47:29,023 --> 00:47:30,548
and tell us.

666
00:47:32,052 --> 00:47:35,370
And if you have to--

667
00:47:35,470 --> 00:47:36,735
stop her.

668
00:47:42,085 --> 00:47:43,918
She's my wife.

669
00:47:48,043 --> 00:47:49,468
I understand.

670
00:47:56,751 --> 00:48:03,466
I left my wife and my
baby boy to be here.

671
00:48:03,566 --> 00:48:05,927
I don't have any immunity.

672
00:48:07,591 --> 00:48:10,311
If I'm arrested, I'm finished.

673
00:48:12,274 --> 00:48:16,897
If they catch me and send me back,

674
00:48:16,996 --> 00:48:19,148
I'll be shot.

675
00:48:21,520 --> 00:48:26,402
I'm here because the
future of our country

676
00:48:26,501 --> 00:48:28,663
is being decided right now.

677
00:48:29,590 --> 00:48:31,722
You know that.

678
00:48:33,884 --> 00:48:37,541
I'm sorry you have to make
some tough decisions, too.

679
00:48:40,231 --> 00:48:42,791
I'll wait to hear from you.

680
00:49:42,531 --> 00:49:45,520
There's all this crap in the
paper about the Summit--

681
00:49:45,619 --> 00:49:47,911
like we're the ones
standing in the way...

682
00:49:48,010 --> 00:49:50,302
You working on it?

683
00:49:53,331 --> 00:49:55,293
It would be good if they made a deal.

684
00:49:55,393 --> 00:49:57,256
Fewer weapons.

685
00:50:00,116 --> 00:50:02,308
Fewer weapons for us, not for them.

686
00:50:03,702 --> 00:50:06,652
They just want to use
these treaties as a cover

687
00:50:06,671 --> 00:50:08,026
so they can keep building
up their arsenal

688
00:50:08,126 --> 00:50:09,750
while we get rid of ours.

689
00:50:09,850 --> 00:50:11,683
That sound fair to you?

690
00:50:12,649 --> 00:50:14,303
What's going on with you?

691
00:50:17,173 --> 00:50:18,627
What do you mean?

692
00:50:18,727 --> 00:50:21,357
Elizabeth, look at you.

693
00:50:25,084 --> 00:50:26,977
You smell like cigarettes all the time.

694
00:50:27,076 --> 00:50:28,730
Your whole way of being seems off.

695
00:50:28,840 --> 00:50:31,340
These past few months,

696
00:50:31,400 --> 00:50:33,154
it feels like it's just
getting worse and worse.

697
00:50:33,253 --> 00:50:36,910
Well, I'm busy, obviously.

698
00:50:37,906 --> 00:50:40,566
It is finally getting to you.

699
00:50:40,666 --> 00:50:42,160
After all these years.

700
00:50:43,426 --> 00:50:45,488
You're amazing--

701
00:50:45,588 --> 00:50:48,218
but it is finally getting to you.

702
00:50:49,842 --> 00:50:52,044
When you told me to
quit, you were right.

703
00:50:52,064 --> 00:50:53,220
It was the best thing I ever did.

704
00:50:53,240 --> 00:50:55,461
And I was thinking...

705
00:50:55,561 --> 00:50:57,075
I'm-- Look.

706
00:50:57,085 --> 00:50:58,889
I'm so tired right now.

707
00:50:59,088 --> 00:51:00,284
Work was...

708
00:51:00,383 --> 00:51:02,745
I-I know. I'm sorry.
Look, I-I just need to--

709
00:51:02,844 --> 00:51:04,239
I have to talk to you about something.

710
00:51:04,339 --> 00:51:07,895
Let's talk tomorrow. I'm--
Honestly, I'm just beat.

711
00:51:07,995 --> 00:51:10,486
I-I know how hard you're working.

712
00:51:10,586 --> 00:51:11,921
I'm not complaining.

713
00:51:12,020 --> 00:51:13,973
This summit is a big deal.

714
00:51:14,083 --> 00:51:15,477
There's a lot to do.

715
00:51:15,577 --> 00:51:17,530
Whatever it is you want to talk about,

716
00:51:17,550 --> 00:51:18,686
we can talk about tomorrow.

717
00:51:18,765 --> 00:51:21,495
Whether it's Henry or
your work, it can wait.

718
00:51:21,595 --> 00:51:23,986
It's not Henry. Today, I--

719
00:51:24,086 --> 00:51:24,953
Whatever it is,

720
00:51:25,052 --> 00:51:25,979
I have to figure out

721
00:51:26,058 --> 00:51:27,573
what the hell is going
on with the Summit

722
00:51:27,672 --> 00:51:29,187
and everything else right now.

723
00:51:29,366 --> 00:51:32,614
So, I know you love to talk,
but you don't have to sit here

724
00:51:32,634 --> 00:51:34,019
and wait for me 'til
1:00 in the morning.

725
00:51:34,129 --> 00:51:36,560
I know how tired you are,
but I need to talk to you.

726
00:51:36,679 --> 00:51:39,877
If you knew how tired I am, you
wouldn't still be talking.

727
00:51:39,977 --> 00:51:41,173
Elizabeth, this-- this job you're doing,

728
00:51:41,272 --> 00:51:43,693
it's-- it's exhausting and
it's complicated and hard.

729
00:51:43,803 --> 00:51:45,696
I don't need another one
of your speeches, Philip.

730
00:51:45,796 --> 00:51:47,320
I need sleep.

731
00:51:47,420 --> 00:51:49,083
Let me sleep.

732
00:51:50,717 --> 00:51:52,770
Great.

733
00:51:52,879 --> 00:51:55,002
Fine, go sleep.

734
00:53:10,652 --> 00:53:13,562
_
